76561198006684815,Not Recommended,268650,27947706,"Posted: 28 November, 2016",all,Chaos,"Let me start off by saying that I think this game is a lot of fun! However, because of the latest changes it's lost one of the great appeals it had for me, and I myself will not be playing the game again, which is a real shame.However, I'll still recommend it for what it is now - a building and combat simulator. It does this really well, but unfortunately due to some of the latest updates, that's all it's become.There used to be things like resource management, fuel management, rarer materials which forced you to build with weaker materials until you could secure better materials, but apparently people whined about not being able to build their huge massive holy crap ships from the word go, heaven forbid, which ate up much of their metal, and so the developer merged all resources into one. Instead of planning how to secure the materials you need/want to build the ships you want and taking over territories based on this - it's now a game of kill everything and do it however you want in any order because it doesn't matter anymore.For example - there used to be fuel, ammo, along with metal, wood, and crystal. This in itself seemed perfectly fine - crystal being a rarer material and more difficult to secure. Fuel and Ammo being separated so if you didn't produce enough of either, you're in trouble. Now, there's no more production of ammo or fuel. All is a single resource, and the whole game is focused around combat alone.Gone are the days of securing resource sites that had stronger resources of metal or crystal to up your supply. That strategic element is gone. Gone are the days of saving up and building smartly with the materials you have available to overcome your enemies. With but one resource, a whole section of the game has been over simplified and it's lost a huge appeal because of it, at least for me. The complexity and planning was one of the things I loved most about it.For many people this is will be a big deal. I told my friend about it and he's agreed - he no longer wants to play simply based on this change alone. We both feel the game is now easy mode. Combat, nothing more.However, it does combat really well. There's great complexity and depth with the ship building itself, even if there's really no point in having materials at all anymore. I'm not entirely sure why the developer even has resources at this point. I do however still recommend the game for the combat alone, even if that's not enough to keep me playing it."
