,Recommended,268650,11832517,"Posted: 23 August, 2014",all,The Malpractice Cactus,"Aright, so here's the thing. This is a great game IF you're willing to sink obsessive amounts of time into it. This is by no means a casual game as there is simply too much content to be absorbed across any number of ten minute sessions. If one isn't willing to make that committment to learning, this game is not for them.Reasons to play this game:+Excellent physics, especially for a voxel box-esque game.+Build literally any sort of vehicle you want. You want a spaceship that doubles as a submarine? No problem.+Story missions that test the depths of one's abilities.+Fully customizable weapons platforms. I don't think of my laser guided missiles so much as missiles as they are long range sea mines that happen to fly.+Intuitive and shockingly convenient vehicle automation.+Nowhere as resource intensive as one would think it would be.Reasons NOT to play this game:-Steep learning curve. Building more than basic boats and engines is not for the faint of heart.-High time commitment.-Build interface is clunky and plays less like a game than a 3D drafting program.-Controls frequently inconvenient and limited in customization.-Stock vehicles for story missions seem unabashedly bad. Namely one critical, otherwise easily fixed flaw, like leaving the driveshaft of a gigantic drill completely exposed..."
