76561198334532254,Recommended,268650,33431068,Posted: 10 July,all,colonelmustardgas3,"Great game with an amazing community. Honestly one of the friendliest player bases I have ever seen.Building ComplexityOn a scale of 1 to 10 in terms of how complex the building is, I would give this a ""Designing a f*cking rocketship"". The game is very in-depth with building and mechanics, but this is not necessarily a bad thing. For the new player, this can be daunting, but the community is always willing to help. As a wise man once said, ""It's not a learning curve, it's a learning brick wall."" Fortunately, once you climb that wall, you start to have some real fun with building.CampaignWhile the Campaign is rather plain and Adventure mode leaves much to be desired, the game is fun to play nonetheless. The beauty of this game is that you can put obstacles in the way of your building to make the game more challenging, and with the wide variety of armors, engines, and weapons, you can always experiment with new play styles. One thing to note, however, is that it is very rare to get large multi-ship battles, simply because there is a volume restriction to prevent setting computer's ablaze. Of course, you can always make smaller ships to allow for more to spawn at any one point, but this mitigates the feel of large battleship on battleship action.MultiplayerThis is in my opinion the least glamorous of all the features of From the Depths. While Multiplayer is definitely enjoyable, as you can play Co-op in campaigns or battle it out with other players, the multiplayer itself is rather lacking. This is an Early Access game (but not really), so bugs are to be expected. However, multiplayer has a plethora of issues, making the gameplay underwhelming."
