76561198334599365,Recommended,268650,26758632,"Posted: 22 November, 2016",all,TheMasterCheese,"My take on From the DepthsFirst, allow me to come out and say this, the developers of this game are on the verge of something big in my opinion. This game is truly special in three ways.1. It balances the complexity with the playability.This is probably the thing I love most about this game. Nothing is all in one piece. Everything from canons, to engines, to AIs must be built by the player, and can be built in any way that the player sees fit. However, at the same time the game is very comprehensive. At first the player may get completely lost in the complexity, but the wide range of tutorials allows for a quick understanding of the games mechanics, and allows the player to get in the game rather quickly.2. It merges sandbox gameplay with strategic gameplay.This game feels as though it is a cross between Minecraft and Command and Conquer. You command the vehicles that you built, and with eight different factions to fight, your strategies and vehicles change constantly to combat your foes strengths, and exploit their weaknesses. Everything you do or build is a strategic choice, which is what primarily makes this game so unique.3. There is plenty of room for creativity.Although the game is widely based on strategy, the block-based building allows for an infinite amount of possibilities as to what the player can create. There are nearly no restrictions on what you can or can’t build...so go ahead, build that flying unicorn you’ve always dreamed of!With qualities like these, the game is bound for greatness. If you (the developers) can maintain these three key traits, then you will likely create an extremely successful game."
