,Recommended,268650,31728849,Posted: 13 May,all,The Average Gamer,"God, were to even Begin. First of all, I give this game a 9/10 personal review score.From the Depths or FtD is obviusly a sandbox but what makes this one diffrent from so many other vehicle and mechanical sand boxes like Scrap Mechanic, Space Engineers, Besige, etc. is that From the depths allows you to build pretty much whatever you want so the only limit is your imagination. In order to make this review shortish, im going to overlook only the main features of the gameCampaign: Campaign mode is really fun if your the stratagy type person who sunk untold hours into MechWarrior or Age of Empires or any sort of Real Time Stratagy game. Its even has some story to it to give the campaign some meanging and ""depth"" (sorry I had to XD). But quick word of advice to any new players, the campaign is long and very hard even on easy difficulty, I reccomend a good 20 hours in the Designer building your fleet before attacking the DWG.Designer Mode: This is were the fun begins. Designer mode acts as creative mode where you have limitless rescources to build your ships & planes & helicopters & tanks & subs & spacecraft & airships & etc., and you can even spawn other ships on other teams to see how well it fights. Its good fun :).Devs. Commitment: FtD is a HUGE GAME which is why its still in early access but definetly worth to grab right now and definetly on a Steam sale. Each update the devs release are always well made and ready to download and play. Theres almost no bugs in the game suprisingly for something of this size which is amazing! And the Devs are always happy to help with technical issues.Probloms :( (every game has them)Theres only 1 really big problom and its the ammount of time it takes to understand and learn how everything works but it is fun to try new ideas even when you have no physical idea how the F*** to build a Cram Cannon or a Laser.playing the game: This is shown in the game itself but I want to show it here so you dont need to buy the game and then find out, There is a Mouse building option and a Keyboard building option, Mouse obviusly works better with people (such as myself) who play games like minecraft or terraria. Keyboard you have to learn how to use, some say that building with keyboard is faster, I dont honestly know cause I'm a mouse person but you can find out for yourself if you do so incline to use the keyboard to build your really big battleship of Ultimite Dread.And that concludes my reviewSorry I didnt make this short, oh well :)"
