76561197967244540,Recommended,268650,24774434,"Posted: 8 August, 2016",all,RinValak,"Very intriguing so far.Unlike most games nowadays, you actually have to learn how to play this game before actually playing it. Luckily, there's a wealth of in-game resources to teach you, including: step-by-step demos, in-game tutorial sessions, and quizzes after each section. Yup. Quizzes. You get EXP for getting questions right.And that's all justified, because FtD is a very complicated and deep game that gives you a ton of flexible tools to play with. Far more difficult to learn than anything like Space Engineers, so if that was too cerebral for you--avoid FtD.I'm still doing tutorials and learning how to play at the time of writing this (5hrs), and I'll write more as I go.EDIT: I still really don't understand how to 'play' the game. Still recommending, just go into it knowing that it's got a very steep learning curve. 2 steep 4 me."
