,Recommended,268650,34421107,Posted: 22 August,all,ChillingCammy,"While I will keep my first review below (it was negative) I've sunk enough hours in to admit I love this game. It wasn't easy to get into and I still think the tutorial and story missions need to be reworked.... ...but geez... this game is cool. It was worth my money for sure.The thing I love most about this game is troubleshooting my design in the builder. Most of my hours have been spent pitting my designs against each other and the built in ships. It's the best feeling to see the more recent version of your favorite destroyer rip the older version to pieces. I have also enjoyed the campaign, although I haven't gotten into it as far as I would like to. Capturing and controlling resource regions (and defending them from marauders...) makes for some of the best strategic gameplay I've played in a while. Seeing your designs succeed against the enemy is so satisfying and great fun.The voxelated building is a great. The variety of blocks lets you build in great detail. I decided to learn the keyboard style vs. mouse style, and while its not perfect it is worth giving a go.The Advance Cannons are VERY cool. While I found them frustrating at first, the satisfaction of figuring out how to implement them was worth the learning curve. While CRAM cannons are simple (yet not ineffective), I really liked the customization of designing my own shells using Advance Cannons. Worth learning to use!Although the AI is customizable I find myself turning off the movement function of the AI and commanding ships myself. The AI is very capable of using weapons but doesn't navigate well. There is an option to write programs to control how ships move (which is pretty sweet) but I'm not so technically inclined. The AI for enemy ships seems pretty well done so this is likely my short coming and not the game's.This game isn't perfect yet I am confident it will improve like a fine wine. I found myself very frustrated at first but kept coming back every day to improve my ships, and to do battle in the campaign. The two hours steam gives you to try this game won't be enough to learn how to play, so check out some gameplay videos before you buy!WRITTEN AUGUST, 2017:About halfway through the tutorial, and I know I'm stuck with the game as I've sunk over 2 hours into it. I want to like it and will keep trying to learn. However, there are a few huge problems with the tutorial (which is definitely necessary to approach a game like this)The format seems counter intuitive. One mission you piece together a component, the next you are looking at a basic 3D model of that component. To present concepts other way around could save much frustration, as knowing which way a piece goes is not always obvious.Randomly I cannot place pieces, specifically on a mission where I am assembling a CRAM turret.Maybe I am just a noob turning off attachment nodes but I have found myself grinding my teeth in rage from it. In addition, I have experienced random units attacking me at inappropriate moments (such as 5 seconds into a tutorial on how to pilot a ship... rebooting the tutorial seems to fix this but it is overwhelming to be sure) (CORRECTION AS OF SEPTEMBER 2017:I WAS A NOOB. PRESS ] TO INTERACT WITH A PART PLACED ON A ROTATION BLOCK)The writing in the stories seems very strange and childish. An early mission has you fixing an engine, while ""your dad listens to ticking missiles and your mother works the pumps""... you're a robot and no one else is aboard the ship. Maybe this will be fleshed out in future releases. This mission was also strange in that you are attacked by pirates and instructed to fire missiles, immediately after coming to grips with piloting the ship. The missiles fly out the back of your vehicle and underwater... it is not at all obvious where you are shooting and if you have hit anything. To top it off, after the mission a quiz question points this out as if it was a good learning opportunity in how not to build missiles. I mean I just learned how to build an engine and can barely pilot a ship, now I'm suppose to digest avoiding pirates, shooting missiles and proper ship design so VERY early in the tutorial? I found it pretty discouraging.I guess my point is the tutorial needs to be reworked. There's too many typos and bugs abound.I'll keep playing, I want to like this game! (I DID KEEP PLAYING. SO WORTH IT)"
