,Recommended,268650,32036637,Posted: 29 May,all,Dead meme,just good fun.
,Recommended,268650,26378959,"Posted: 2 November, 2016",all,GOUST,"From the Depths-	Not many games allow for such in depth vehicle customization and versatility as From the Depths. In this world of endless possibilities you are placed inside the body of a very creative protagonist robot named ""Rambot"" who is given a roll dependant of his situation. There is multiple campaigns to play through, all vary in difficulty, story, enviroments, and enemies. Along side the story mode, there is the vehicle designer where you are able to create and test your various inventions. Starting to feel lonely? Yes!? Well, there is also a multiplayer mode where you can play exclusive gamemodes with your pals!-	From the Depths has limitless creation possibilities. If you can think of any Helicopter, Jet, Boat, Battleship, Submarine, Tank, or Fortress, chances are that you can build it, and have it be piloted by an AI, or yourself alternativly. Along with being able to create your own monstrosities, which they probably will be at first, you can also build *almost* 1:1 scale replicas of any real vehicle. With the wide variaty of 400 different blocks, many different materials, and millions of different gun creation possiblities.-	With being able to create anything you can imagine, there are also very many ways to put your inventions to the test! With the 4 campaigns to play through, there are hundreds of thousands of hours of content to be played, though it must be noted that the campaign modes can be buggy and unplayable on occasion. With that being said, there are various enviroments to explore. ""Neater"" is the most complete planet with a very large and complex story driven campaign where you must defeat all of the opposing forces and grow your army of Artificial Inteligence controlled vehicles. You will face very many different factions that have their own building style and stories alike. This campaign may take hundreds of hours to complete, it is all dependant on how fast you learn to create effective combat machines, and manage resources.-	There is also a very incomplete multiplayer mode where you can play with as many friends as you'd like... or handle! There are very many party modes to play such as; Tower defence. In the Tower Defence mode, you must hold down a tower from various enemies with limited resources, so you must think quick. You may also battle Artificial Intelligence controlled vehicles with your own vehicles with the company of others. Campaign mode is also availible to play with your friends if you'd like.-	From the Depths is truely a unique game with very a creative solution to the vehicle/voxel building game genere as a whole. With endless building possibilities, hundreds of different blocks, and lots of weaponry options. Not only is the game fun to play around with, it has an incredible amount of campaign and story content to explore and learn about, with many different worlds, and variety of enviroments. With more updates, From the Depths is slowly getting even better, with lots more interesting content being added monthly. The developer truely loves his game and cares about what the community has to say, taking any- and all advice and seeing if it would fit the game. After 280+ hours invested into the game as of writing this review, I can say I will be playing this game for many years to come!"
