,Recommended,268650,20903311,"Posted: 1 February, 2016",all,Admiral Obvious,"I love this game so far, and the process/progress so far that has been done by this developer.Very rarely do you get a developer that actually responds to suggestions. This game alone can be considered a gem for that reason in my opinion.The game itself is a voxel style build e'm up. You can literally build anything from spaceships, submarines, battleships, helicopters, hot air baloons, and more, as is evident in the game description. As long as it makes sense in terms of physics, and common sense, you can build it.Admittedly, the game is very complex. Most get turned off by the ammount of completely this game has (as you can tell by the majority of negative reviews). I admit, I was too. Uninstalled the game after about 2 hours of trying and failing to build a dinghy. Came back to it a month later, and haven't stopped since.The designer mode, for me at least is where most of the game is, as I like to play around with the mechanics of the game, especially since they change almost every other day on the dev test build which I'm subscribed to.The campaign mode is relatively simple, but pretty fun. At the moment, just ""kill everyone"" to win. It takes a quite long time to do this, so you needn't worry about that.Edit: The developers are currently implimenting scaled down campaigns, so instead of you versus everyone, you get to be one of the base factions against a different faction.To be fair, there is no real sense of ""balance"" in the game. That's not to be taken as a bad way. Everything you, and your enemy has has a hard counter designed specifically to beat it. Enemy has cannons? Use shields. Enemy has shields? Use missiles. Enemies have missiles? Use lasers. Enemies have lasers? Use smokescreens.The only potential issues with this game at the moment of this review are that it still uses the slightly antiquated Unity 4 engine, and the bugs/performance that goes with it.The only other, honestly fair issue is the lack of depth in the tutorials. They cover the bare basics, and that's about it. Admittedly the game gets updated basically every other day, so it's going to be pretty hard to nail down a tutorial until you at least get close to finishing the game, and I won't hold that against the developer, especially since the in game encyclopedia-learning center leads you out to all the resources you can think of to learn the game.The community is small, but very active, and helpful, as is attested by the size of the workshop, and always will help you with any issues you may have with this game.I would wholeheartedly reccomended this game at full price, and even more so at sale price.P.S. My review doesn't cover multiplayer. It's usually unstable, and largely unfinished, so I'm not able to fairly justify a review of it. It works until people start to desync, and then it usually breaks down. This isn't a game that's designed around multiplayer, but may be in the future."
