,Recommended,268650,15699621,"Posted: 5 May, 2015",all,angerydad.jpeg,"This game... If you own Kerbal, imagine like you're trying to build a boat in Kerbal, a game about constructing space ships and space planes. This game is basically that, trying to construct boats in a game about spaceships. Seriously though, it's not an easy game, but it sure is fun. All of my hours thus far have just been in the vehicle builder, trying to build an small efficient boat is hard enough, once you get that part somewhat down, you need to account for weapons and protection, which is another whole learning curve in itself. I haven't even gotten into multiplayer or even any campaign or story yet, only because I'm still learning how to build.. You need to build the engines, the boats to use these sucessfully, and even build your own weapons. But it sure as hell keeps you hooked. You can even build sky/land/sea fortresses, planes, helicopers and all, which I can't even imagine because I still struggle with boats.. Maybe one day.tl;dr: If you like games that allow a huge amount of creativity, and that have a challenge/learning curve, and you like games with 100% freedom, this game is for you."
