76561198275035125,Recommended,268650,28281726,"Posted: 9 December, 2016",all,A Paper Builder,"With over 180 hours as I write this, I figured I should give it a review (I'll update it when the full version comes out). The game has a massive learning curve, but it's a lot of fun once you learn it. The new tracking system is ineresting, and realistic, but annoying. I figure you need about 20+ hours of gameplay, several youtube tutorials and steam guides. The weapons are easy enough to grasp, once you understand them. The game is the most fun towards the end of the campaigns and the sandbox mode, where you have near unlimited resources to fuel an overly powerful war machine. The large explosions are always fun to watch, especially one of the HMS Ragnorak turrets, although it is rare (on the workshop, creation by Robbaz). Well worth the time and money, especially if you got it on sale. I would highly reccomend this. Have fun!IGN 7.8/10 Too much water"
