,Recommended,268650,17477058,"Posted: 10 August, 2015",all,Thunderstruck,"From the Depths is an Early access Game (as of review) with not only alot of potential, but with alot of that potential already in the game. The premise is simple, build fighting craft and duke it out, once you start to play you realise it isn't that simple. From engines to custom guns it has a very steep learning curve but theres something about building that more effecient engine and that new triple barreled gun that is so satisfying, especially when you're bearing down on an enemy that can only hope to dent you. With the campaign and some story modes in the game there is so much to do for an early access. The story are set missions you need to accomplish, this are recommended for people with a bit more experience in the game though. The campaign is the first stop after building ships in the ship designer (with a brilliant keyboard build mode) the campaign pits you against other factions in a fight for the planet, you start off with one base and one boat but soon start to build up your fleet as you attack and defend to capture more resource points scattered around the map. This is where most of my time has been spent so far, even when you get defeated by a new airship that your enemy has developed its ok, because you go back to the drawing board and design something to counter it. All in all this is a fantastic game that i predict will become a huge success and I hope it does. I can't recommend it enough. The only thing I can find as an issue is the crashing, there can be quite a lot. They either need to fix the crashing or add an autosave as soon as possible. theres nothing worse than losing a large ship because you forgot to save."
,Recommended,268650,17493520,"Posted: 11 August, 2015",all,KalkiKrosah,"TL;DR Version: It's like lego wars for adults. If you like legos and are an adult then you will like this game.This is not a game that you will pick up immediately. I have spent maybe 30 hours on this game to just build stuff and learn how to use advanced weaponry and how to configure it properly. I still have a lot more to go before I can jump right into campaign and become effective. This game is called ""From the Depths"" and there is a great deal of depth in how to set up your ships, structures, air planes, helicopters and space crafts. There's also fleet commands, AI functions and ""diplomacy."" This game will take up a lot of time if you want to be good at it but there is definitely replay value involved in the game, complex algorithms at work and frequent updates and patches being made.The developers of this game put in a lot of effort to make this game work and it really shows. They continue to make frequent updates, patches and additions into the game.So if you can afford the time needed to learn the game then its worth getting because it will be a game you come back to many times in the future."
76561197974171618,Recommended,268650,17506384,"Posted: 12 August, 2015",all,tyrrell82,"This game, in early access, is already very good. However, it may not be for some.To enjoy this game, one has to be very creative and enjoy tweaking and testing literally everything... and I mean everything.Example, I've had to design my missiles so that the longer range missiles have enough fuel to reach their target, and that there is enough coordination with the short range missile boosters to reach a longer range target. I've also encorporated a proximity sensing IR-Missile so that even if there is a small miss, the missile will still go off. Next, i've made the payload an  explosive compliment and a very limited shrapanel compliment to ensure that with the added penetration the acceleration of the missile provides, that when it hits something it will do more isolated damage.This is justified by shorter range missiles that i've had a reduced explosive yeild, but are highly maneuverable at the expense of longer range and explosive layout... And this discription my friends is JUST the missiles. Literally everything requires tweaking, thought and planning.For me, this is great. It takes a while to figure out and one feels a sense of accomplishment when something works.Expect to become heavily invested in a design and the continuous modifications required to produce a good weapons platform.Casual gamers. Pass on this one. Hardcore gamers... Pick it up already!"
