76561198029735322,Recommended,268650,22304747,"Posted: 8 April, 2016",all,Coyote Jim,"From the Depths has been one of the most rewarding games I have ever played. It is rewarding because there is a lot of complex aspects of the game that take time to learn, but once you learn them, you kind of feel like the master of the universe. Seriously, when you build a ship that only uses 1000 blocks, and that 1000 block ship can take out a 7000 block monster ship, you will sit back and make those two ships fight over and over and you will be just as excited the 100th time you duel them as you were the first time.My most favorite thing about the game is that it is such blank canvas. You can create and design your war death machines any way you would like. The sky is the limit (well actually space is the limit, yes you can build space craft). SO many possibilities. My style is typically extremely fast small craft with only one large weapon mounted to them, think of my ships and aircraft as fast gun carriers. But that is just one of thousands of possibilities. Some people like to re-create EVE Online ships. Some folks like to build battleships that are so huge it takes them weeks to do so. I love to just download other people's designs and have a look at all the crazy things people come up with. I always come away with new cool ideas to integrate into my designs when I do this.So, the learning curve. Yep, it’s there, and it’s steep. It is not impassable though. Like other games in this genre you will have to put in a little work in order to learn it. Post questions on the forums (fantastic community there by the way), watch Youtube videos, have a look at the wiki...those kinds of things. The in-game tutorials are getting better and better, so you may not have to do quite so much homework as you did a year ago.If you are reading this, then you must at least like building games or sandbox games. If that describes you, then this is definitely the game for you."
