,Recommended,268650,19339289,"Posted: 28 November, 2015",all,Cpt_Seagull,"So I'm going to be honest about this review. Sure I recommend this game - but only to those who are willing to put time into researching the basics of the game or are willing to try, fail, try fail, try, fail and eventually succeed. I can't really say mutch about the learning curve of the game, as I had watched 5+ hours of footage bofore even looking at the game's store page. From what I've read of the negative reviews of this game the overwhelming majority of people have less than 10 hours in-game and they complain about the lack of a tutorial (there is one, if you look). And the clunky UI and controls. Sure, if you don't like the UI, that's your choice - but those who are used to the UI will most likely agree with me when I say it's quite informative. As for the controls - yes they can be a little offputting at times, and currently not rebindable (I'm sure this will be added at a later date) but like the rest of the game - you get used to them. Oh, there is a mouse building mode (much like minecraft or space engineers) and that may fix your problems.Now, onto why I think this game is great:+The game has surprising amounts of depth (pun intended)+Encourages creativity in designs+Very expansive campaign mode+Useful building tools+Whilst only haveing a few types of basic block, there is a very wide variety of types of said base materials+Nothing is indestructableNow, some of the negatives:-People may not like the learning curve-The game recently became much more complex with the advanced cannons-Non-rebindable controls (will remove when added)"
