,Recommended,268650,20127033,"Posted: 30 December, 2015",all,Bicky,"Wow. Just wow.This game is proof that there is a better side of Early Access. However be aware, performance problems with this game are common. Even the most powerful system will struggle to run it at it's full settings.That being said..Positives:Building is fairly simple for the most partThe game explainsNEARLYeverything to you. Trust me, you'll need it for the first 6 or so hours.Depth, depth, and more depth. This is a complex game, and that's exactly what you want with it. It lets you do so much.Simple building* - There is a Minecraft-like mode but the keyboard controls are fantastic. Rapid building w/o much effort.Sandbox. Do whatever you want.Editor.     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^AI. A game this complex has to have a powerful AI system to go with it and it delivers.Combat Satisfying for the most part. Damage is incredibly apparent and everything other than terrain can be destroyed.This is aCHALLENGINGgame. Do not let it fool you. The factions can be brutal. [See negatives however]Customizeability allows you do make pretty much anything you wantDev team is active. They regularly listen to the community and have been for around 2 years now.Fun. Fun fun and more fun. It's hard to stop enjoying this game.Designs. The guys who designed the ships did a fantastic job. Every ship is completely different from the next, and theres A LOOOOOOT of vehicles in the gameNegatives:Performance is pretty bad. Last time I checked pretty sure it only supported 1 core. One of the games where CPU is more important than GPU currently. Yah...Horrible engine slow down effect. If you've ever played Supreme Commander you know how bad this can be.Detail options are nonexistant. It's the standard Fastest to Fantastic detail settings and it resets every time you play. There are options like bullet trails and particle effect sliders that can help but it doesn't change too much.Overwhelmingly brutal difficulty sometimes, especially with the new advanced cannon updateUnbalanced weapons. Lasers ruin the game. Period. They're boring, they obliterate anything from any range in a few seconds with just 1 beam, let alone multiple ones. Regardless of that, they have terrible visual feedback when they fire. This is my second biggest complaint with this game and can be a complete dealbreaker. Advanced cannons and railguns have so many broken points about them as well but it's nowhere near as bad as lasers.Scarlet Dawn and Lightning Hoods. They nearly exclusively use lasers and they use A LOT of them. Very very big ones. They are undoubtedly the worst factions. Cool designs, but man. Not the slightest bit fun to fight.Lasers lasers lasers I can't stress this enough. The defenses against them completely destroy the aesthetics of your ship in a game where aesthetics and player creativity are the most important thing.This is a time sink. If you don't have much time in your day to play a game, don't even bother with this one unless it's all you want.Learning is a pain for the first 6 or 7 hours. Controls feel clunky at first and the complexity can be a hurdle to get over.Player can be tempted to build sattelites or literal space ships. I don't recommend this as Scarlet Dawn are the only faction that use this and can counter it well. Again, this is mostly due to lasers being the only viable thing in space.The UI is horrible for a new player.Though there are many many ships in the game, you probably wont see a quarter of them due to how early game they are.Needs more worlds honestly. Have the same settings as Neter but with the factions moved around specifically to stop the problem mentioned above.I honestly can't think of anything else.All in all, I'm 38 hours in after playing for a week and I'd say it's definitely worth it.However, lasers in this are like Artillery in World of Tanks. They just don't belong in the game. They purely take away from gameplay and enjoyment. I'm hoping they are flatout removed rather than just nerfing or changing.I'm pretty sure performance omtimization is one of the later steps of a game's development and this is still adding quite a bit.Performance improvements would fix a lot. One core support is horrid."
