76561197971903663,Recommended,268650,25027289,"Posted: 20 August, 2016",all,drinsano,"From the Depths is very much a ""Work in Progress"" title in Steam's early access.  By this I mean that the game is currently playable, but unrefined.  The developers are releasing a fairly regular stream of updates and bugfixes, and many of the nuances of the game are in flux.  The learning curve of this game is exponential, though the in game resources for new players are improving.All of that said, From the Depths represents a fantastic concept in gaming.  The core concept of an RTS in which units are designed by users is pushed to its logical extreme in FtD, and I have great confidence in the dedication and competence of the developers to see the project through.So, long story short:  If you like painstakingly building things, and you like RTS games:  Buy this game.  It's not for the faint of heart, but the game's best appeal may be to players who believe that part of the fun of a game is in learning to play it."
