76561198028877049,Recommended,268650,23468125,"Posted: 9 June, 2016",all,Sea Serpent Named Nessie,"Let me start this off with that the most played game I have on Steam is Planetside 2 and I've had it for 3-4 years and played it on and off for long period of time. That now said, I've managed to get to 100 hours within the first month of me getting this game and am currently at the 200+ mark which is nearing itself closer to being Planetside 2 which as a gamer I've played quite a bit of. That in itself should tell you how awesome this game is.Either way lets really start this off. Have you even wanted to play a game like minecraft but had more moving parts and gizmos that aren't just pistons or buggy/poorly implemented mods? Guess what From the Depths is what you are looking for. The resource system is different than minecraft in that you have stored resoures of a few types such as metal, natural (wooden), crystals and etc. Which can be used to craft together different types of crafts ranged from a death laser barg to even space ships with orbital ordinance, or even maybe you like fluffy sheeps that happen to swim to the enemy and may or may not swing a hammer causing massive damage like some users have made. Hell the game normally has an angry chicken flying craft with cannons and missles.Are you creative? Well you really can't get bored with this game because the limit is how much you can think of building or if you aren't creative guess what. There is a massive sharing of things called blueprints which are other players or your own crafts. You don't need to build a good ship when someone else has already done it for you, or maybe you wanna build a better one than them!You can play this game in so many ways its silly. You can just sit in the designer making what ever you want. Maybe you wanna face off other players which you can do in multiplayer which is still in development and comes with its slew of problems but most are minor or not even noticable. You know what I hate. Games that give me only a single player experience but let me have a useless companion follow me around or even force said uselss companion on me, guess what From the Depths doesn't do. Limit you to just having useless companions but also useless friends too! Unless you happen to be the useless one but either way you can game either by yourself or play the FULL game with a friend or even play a community made world.The only issue this game has currently is the UI needs some work and the game can be too much for new players at the start, its a very deep game and its not gonna hold your hand too well. Anyone who gets this game, I recommend you try to make it through the first 10-20 hours of gameplay before you give up. This is around the time things click and you can start making awesome crafts. That may seem like a long time to play the game but it flew by for me and many others I've talked to about the starting of the game online with.Oh and if you are worried about it being abandoned. The dev 'Nick Smart' does regular updates and recently expended the staff to more than just himself. He works very hard on this game and is very vocal with the community on the games own webpage. Every update seems to bring new and better candy."
