76561197984308168,Recommended,268650,24292713,"Posted: 13 July, 2016",all,Stook,"Complex, complex, and fun.The ""keyboard"" building mechanics are fantastic once you get used to them, but that takes a couple hours.  The art style is pleasing, especially the engines.  The gameplay is very tough, but rewarding.  I agree with many other reviews that the campaign is too difficult, especially if you are new to the game, and AI/weapons controllers are often inept or dumb.  The game can be obscenely complicated; the PID block is reliant on calculus (or guesswork) and the LUA module is reliant on coding knowledge.  I can not comment on multiplayer.It's a fun game for those into min/max-ing or building in general, but expect to put in a few hours to get anywhere.  A boat will take anywhere from an hour to a week to build."
