76561197991959229,Recommended,268650,33048694,Posted: 30 June,all,Gessie,"In short:Do you love voxel games? Do other voxel games feel too simple? Do you enjoy spending many diligent hours on a single vehicle design in a game? Would you keep playing when it turns out your vehicle is awful and you have to start over?If so you absolutely have to play From the Depths; it's unique and immensely satisfying. Otherwise, save yourself a headache - and I mean that literally.The Good- 100% unique game thanks to a specific feature: Adding AI to your vehicles. There's nothing like it.- More simultaneous vehicle-based carnage than any other voxel game, limited only by your CPU and patience.- Deep tactical consideration when building and fighting with endless possibilities.- Since the game is a single man's pet project at its core, it will remain in development for an undetermined amount of time. Updates are small but steady.The Neutral-The game's general complexity is a niche. Not good or bad, just really specific. If you don't like math and math-related terms, stay away from this game. It requires mild study to become decent at. On the plus side, you'll learn what a PID-controller is while playing a game.- FtD has beennoticeably optimizedsince its early days, but still lags in many campaign encounters on a high end PC. All voxel games lag.The bad-The UI and aesthetics are bad- indisputably so. It's headache-inducing. The UI literally looks like a toddler designed it, and despite many complaints and examples on the forums, including my own, this was never fixed. You can Google screenshots of the UI; see for yourself. The developer is highly inexperienced in the field of game design - and it shows.-Building, both in terms of the editor and the block functions themselves, is unnecessary cumbersome compared to other games. An extreme example is the LUA-controller block, which allows the player, or volunteer developer, to inject his own LUA code.-Language use in the game is extremely poor.Errors everywhere, poorly written lore and ambiguous descriptions - it's really bad.-The communityis somewhat toxic and poorly managed, including the aforementioned language issues. Many are fiercely fanatical about keeping the game the way it currently is, which is substandard."
