,Recommended,268650,33423684,Posted: 9 July,all,Knux,"I have a question that pertains to whether you can appreciate the game, and another pertaining to whether you will.Can you hold large amounts of spatial information in focus simultaneously using your mind's eye?Do you use this skill to build and manipulate complex objects in your head for fun?The complexity ceiling is unreal.  So far I've learned how to build engines really well, as well as exactly one shell size of one caliber of one type of gun.  There is still so much left to learn, and an impossible amount left to master, and for this I am endlessly glad.  It is perhaps the best example of emergent gameplay I can think of: an intricate system built on a small number of simple rules.  Learn the rules, learn the implications, learn the interplay, and try not to get a migraine.I'm very proud of my 3-barreled, recoiless, maximum guage, 180 rpm advanced cannon and its refined assortment of 3 shell types.  Now to mount it in an airship and rain down death from above.  Now I need to learn how to build airships.  Here's to another 60 hours!"
