76561198033825435,Recommended,268650,23337391,"Posted: 1 June, 2016",all,toanderson,"From the Depths feels to me like Kerbal Space Program meets Mount and Blade. Like KSP, you have super-creative, nearly limitless vehicle design and physics-based gameplay. Like M&B, there are huge epic battles and a sandbox-style campaign where you can conquer your enemies and take over their holdings and such.You can make motorboats, sailboats, planes, tanks, spaceships, submarines, aircraft carriers, helicopters, towers, fortresses, or whatever you want. You can arm them with infrared missiles, laser guided missiles, railguns, explosive shells, old-school cannons, or even a ram. And then you can send them out to fight enemies and see how they perform.This is in a great state for early access. I consider it a totally complete game experience already. It's a little rough around the edges and there are some skeletal features not quite developed yet, but it is definitely continuing to be developed and new stuff is released all the time.The Good:Building your vessels is like playing with legos, and you have total freedom in your creativity.Giant slow-mo explosions.Pretty well balanced for an in-development early access game.Interesting and diverse enemy ship designs.Surprisingly versatile and smart AI system. I usually just let it do the work, and there are tons of stuff you can tweak.Technology levels range from cannons and wooden sailing ships to lasers and spaceships.The Bad:Needs a better tutorial and manual. That said, it makes sense to not spend a lot of time there before you're feature complete, and there are tons of youtube guides out there.Landscape is a little clunky. Islands are oddly lumpy, and there is no life anywhere which is oddly clashing with the lore you can read about the different factions.The Ugly:The in-game lore says I'm a son of a family of fishermen or some such, but I'm clearly this weird robot dude and there are no fish anywhere. Nor any tentacle monsters either, despite the game icon. Are we going to get tentacle monsters in future updates? Because I am totally down with that."
