,Recommended,268650,28515125,"Posted: 21 December, 2016",all,TheHamburglar72,"This game is one of the most fun games that I have played in a long time. It's gameplay is extremely addicting and satisfying, through it's nearly endless customization options. You can either build your ship from the ground up, or load a prebuilt design by another player and sail the high seas to your heart's content. While this game is fun once you learn how to play it, it is very complex and requires time and patience to learn how the game works and all the keys to do everything. In addition, make sure your CPU is well equipped to handle this extremely physics heavy game. Hopefully the developers will create some form of update that improves overall performance, but it is currently playable as long as you use lower settings for larger ships such as the HMS Pilkington or HMS Ragnarok by Robbaz. Overall, From the Depths is a difficult, but rewarding/addicting game that is well worth it's asking price. I look foward to future updates and hope that this game will recieve the attention and praise it so rightfully deserves. 9.5/10"
