76561198017565499,Recommended,268650,24258456,"Posted: 11 July, 2016",all,The Fod,"Whilst people may compare it to Minecraft intitially - and the art style is similar, my experience with the game make me think it's more comparable to kerbal space program and/or space engineer.It features several campaigns where it plays like a naval RTS - you gather resources, build units and attack NPC factions to expand territory, the usual stuff.Where this game differs is that you can (if you want to) design all of your units from the ground up - this means you can design literally everything on the vehicle, form the engine, to the guns, to it's AI behaviour.This gives the game a very steep learning curve - but there are, like Kerbal Space Program, many good tutorial videos on youtube, an in game tutorial, and if all else fails, steam workshop support if you want to copy & paste in a certain system that someone else has desgined (this is very handy for guns and engines especially).Overall it's very complex and kinda hard to get into, but once you do it's really satisfying in a siminlar manner to Kerbal."
