76561198073931344,Recommended,268650,17209207,"Posted: 24 July, 2015",all,Funkyman8887,"I find the game fun, creative and entertaining. There are many brilliant designs on the steam workshop and the awesome battles just make the game better. The campaign can be difficult, especially if you are not careful with resources and do not bother with the diplomacy menu (you are enemies with a faction from the start).You can upgrade the character using points from levels which I find very interesting. I would not think that would exist in a game like this but it does and thhe devs have done it well. It is unfinished as some 'attributes' are not implemented but the weapons and skills can come in good use very quickly.Missiles, cannons and lasers are HIGHLY customisable. You can make missiles a certain length and make parts of a missile funtion differently. e.g. Make it 4 blocks long with a thruster, fuel tank, heat seeker and emp to make a small, heatseeking emp missile. You can create giant lasers with an advanced AI to shoot lasers from high up into space (Yes, there is a point high up in the air where you can place a craft and it will float without going up or down unless you use thrusters or push it.)You can create your own cannons to shoot down aircraft or act as a giant anti-ship gun. Or if you don't have much space/ don't know how to work these things you can use the simple weapons. Just one click and then you have a small missile/ laser/ cannon/ torpedo.The heartstones can be a bit of a pain in missions so do NOT bother with it in the campaign. The player has a limited 'charge' and the heartstones fill that up to keep the player alive. Unless you want to play the game in a restricted way do not enable these. Not enabling these will also make boarding and capturing ships a lot easier (only to be scrapped using the scrapper and the resources going to be used for a bigger 'project').Apart from the steep learning curve and complicated controls that are a bit hard to learn then all I have to say is...BUY THIS GAME(P.S. get a good CPU. The game can be demanding in huge battles or even just having one large ship.. Also some things can be very complicated and confusing just to try to get it to work.)"
